 Chimera 2.0 Tutorial: Downloading Chimera<body>
 

 Downloading Chimera 

   
Download Chimera 2.0 Beta from the following site:
  
Chimera 2.0 Software page 
 
If you just want the Java byte-code file for Chimera 2.0b1, just download
the link labeled:
 
Chimera Class Files
 

  This links allows you to download the chimera.jar contains all the 
Java byte-code for Chimera 
2.0 Beta.  This is what you need to run Chimera.  You may place 
it anywhere you like.  A convenient spot would be a location you commonly
place your Java classes for your other Java programs.
 

 
You must then set the chimera.jar file up to be included in the 
CLASSPATH of your Java interpretor.  
 

  Look at the following links to see how you can set up your CLASSPATH to 
include the path to the chimera.jar file you have just downloaded:
 
   
	Setting CLASSPATH in Solaris to include chimera.jar
	   

      
	Setting CLASSPATH in Windows NT to include chimera.jar
	   
   Note: Later on you will need to download client applications which 
will need to be placed in your CLASSPATH as well.  
 

  You are now ready to start the Chimera website.
 

</body> 